't found, this was causing some users problems.  <br>     EQAnnounce now keeps checking every second until it can find the NOTES.TXT file.  <br>     Once it is found it doesn't continue this behaviour, however, it is important to get <br>     the file created using a /NOTE command in the game as soon as possible, as the <br>     added disk activity might cause some in-game performance issues until you do.<br><br>  2) 'Settings' now saved.<br><br>     Now all the selections in the application, selected from the user interface or issued <br>     via #EQA commands are now stored to the registry and reloaded upon running again.<br><br>  3) Command-Line parameters are no longer used.<br><br>  4) Timer 'Max Reminders' and 'Reminder delays' have been added.  These are optional<br>     parameters added to the following #EQA commands:  #EQASPAWN.START, #EQASPELL.START, <br>     #EQASKILL.START, and #EQAEVENT.START.<br><br>     The old syntax:<br>     /note #EQASPAWN.START.A Ghoul Sage.00:28:30.00:00:30<br><br>     The new syntax:<br>     /note #EQASPAWN.START.A Ghoul Sage.00:28:30.00:00:30.3.30<br><br>---------------------------------------------------------^^^^^------ is optional<br><br>     This would imply: &quot;Remind me a maximum of 3 times, waiting 30 seconds between each<br>     reminder&quot;.<br><br>  5) The Damage Calculator has been improved.  It now supports Beastlords and their Warders<br>     and includes the warder damage as if it were their own.  With this, a new parameter has<br>     been added to help determine the pet's proc damage (since it is based on the owner's<br>     level).  It is an optional parameter.<br>  <br>     The old syntax:<br>     /note #EQADAMAGE.START<br><br>     The new syntax:<br>     /note #EQADAMAGE.START.50<br><br>--------------------------^^^------ is optional<br><br>  6) Added in-game 'voiced' help.  No more trying to remember all the commands available to<br>     an object.  The following new commands are now available:<br><br>     #EQAHELP<br>     #EQATSPAWN.HELP<br>     #EQATSPELL.HELP<br>     #EQATSKILL.HELP<br>     #EQATEVENT.HELP<br><br>     #EQADAMAGE.HELP<br>     #EQAWKEYWORD.HELP<br>     #EQALOG.HELP<br>     #EQASPEECH.HELP<br><br>  7) Damage monitoring now dumps to a grid on a *NEW* tab, called 'Damage Grid'.  This can<br>     be copied to the clipboard via Ctrl+C, or Right-Clicking the grid, then selecting <br>     'Copy all to clipboard'.<br><br>  8)  With the addition of a grid displaying mob data, I decided to allow the application to<br>     now be resized, or the edges stretched.  The tab area and grid will now grow <br>     accordingly.  So if you don't have enough screen real-estate to show all the data now<br>     being shown, by all means - make EQAnnounce's application window bigger!<br><br>  9) With the addition of a grid displaying mob data, some users may find it more<br>     productive to not even have the Text-To-Speech engine render information about how they<br>     are performing in-game.  They might just want to take the data after they exit the game<br>     off of the grid and copy it into a spreadsheet program for further analysis.  I added<br>     two new commands to the #EQASPEECH object that now allow &quot;speaking&quot; to be turned on or <br>     off completely.  These are as follows:<br><br>     #EQASPEECH.ON<br>     #EQASPEECH.OFF<br>     <br>     With this feature, the appropriate menus, status bar indicators were added as well.<br>     This setting will be stored and will be reloaded each time the application starts up.<br><br> 10) Case-Sensitivity on objects and commands...  NO MORE!  iSsuE tHeM iN wHaTeveR fOrM yOU<br>     LiKe!!!!<br><br><br><br>BUG FIXES:<br>-------<br><br>  1) Heals in the Damage Calculator should now not throw it off.<br><br>  2) DPS = Total Damage in the Damage Calculator should be working ok now.<br><br>  3) #EQADAMAGE.STOP wouldn't ever turn off the damage monitor.<br><br>  4) #EQALOG.RESET now properly turns off log monitoring, then reloads log monitoring from <br>     the most recent log file found (forcing a player log file switch when the new file has <br>     changed.  Useful when switching characters.)<br><br>     It also announces the log file it stopped using and the new one that it feels is 'the<br>     most current'.<br><br>  5) The way mobs were being tracked when damage was done to them sometimes could get out <br>     of synchronization.  A good example of this is if two mobs were pulled and you were <br>     beating on both at the same time.  All the damage done up until the point of the first<br>     mob being killed would have been counted as damage done to that mob.  It should now<br>     keep the appropriate damage with the appropriate mob.<br><br><br> <p><table><tr><td><p><select name="characters" style="font-size: 14; font-family: verdana, arial; color: #80ffff; background-color: black;"><br><option selected>Glimwin Nettlefoot -- 58 Halfling Druid<br><option>Ssytherak Naz'Ghul -- 54 Iksar Necromancer<br><option>Kaelissa Kedgebane -- 53 Human Monk<br><option>Kaelen Nettlefoot -- 51 Halfling Druid<br><option>Braeus Stoneheart -- 50 Dwarf Cleric<br><option>Nervrak Ka`Vhal -- 50 Dark-Elf Enchanter<br><option>Sharvae Ka`Vhal -- 48 Vah Shir Beastlord<br><option>Kaelystia Naz'Ghul -- 41 Dark-Elf Necromancer<br><option>Kaelax Nettlefoot -- 40 Halfling Warrior<br><option>Graakx Gum'Bones -- 35 Troll Warrior<br><option>Ssythlyss Scalefists -- 30 Iksar Monk<br><option>Vaerysla Do'Vrae -- 29 Erudite Enchanter<br><option>Blik Stik -- 28 Halfling Rogue<br></select></p></td></tr></table></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub92.ezboard.com/uglimwinnettlefoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glimwin Nettlefoot</A> at: 1/9/02 7:02:58 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">